settings.title: What is Sea Moss?
settings.text: Sea Moss is a type of seaweed/algae believed to boost your immune health by helping prevent and relieve cold and flu-like symptoms. It is found on the Atlantic coastlines of North America/Europe, and the Carribean Islands. Irish Sea Μοss has been used for generations in places like Ireland, Scotland, and Jamaica in food and healing remedies. Sea Moss is most commonly known for its anti-inflammatory, anti-aging, anti-bacterial, and anti-viral properties.

settings.title: Iron
settings.content:
Sea moss is a natural source of iron, which is the key mineral involved in oxygen transport and energy production.

Sufficient iron levels can help prevent the early iron-deficiency anemia, a condition characterized by fatigue and low energy levels.

settings.title: Iodine
settings.content: Sea moss is a natural source of iodine, which is important in it’s collaboration with thyroid function. The thyroid gland is a cool and important thing, which  produces hormones that regulate metabolism, including brain metabolism. Adequate iodine levels are essential for optimal brain function and cognitive development.

settings.title: Magnesium
settings.content: is a big boss in muscle contraction and relaxation, supporting healthy muscle function and reducing muscle cramps and spasms. It is multitasking : it also help to optimise energy production and improving nervous system, preventing such things as anxiety and PA.

settings.title: Dietary fiber
settings.content: Sea moss is a rich source of dietary fiber, which is highly  important for maintaining healthy digestion, regulating bowel movements, and supporting gut health.

settings.title: Sulfur
settings.content: Sulfur is an essential mineral that supports the production of keratin, a protein that is a key component of skin, nails, and hair. It may help strengthen the hair and nails and contribute to clear and healthy skin.

settings.title: Mucilage
settings.content: Sea moss contains mucilage, a gel-like substance that forms when it comes into contact with water. Mucilage has a soothing effect on the digestive tract, potentially helping to alleviate irritation and inflammation in conditions like gastritis, ulcers, and acid reflux.

settings.title: Omega-3 Fatty Acids
settings.content: Sea moss contains omega-3 fatty acids, which are known for their cardio benefits and potential support for brain health and inflammation management.

settings.title: Zinc
settings.content: Zinc is involved in the production of new skin cells and plays a role in maintaining the integrity of the skin and nails. It is also involved in the synthesis of proteins and DNA, which is important for hair growth and strength.

settings.title: Calcium
settings.content: Sea moss is a good source of calcium, a mineral essential for building and maintaining strong bones. Calcium is a crucial component of bone structure and helps support bone density and strength.

settings.question: Where is our sea moss from?
settings.answer:
We are proud to say that our sea moss is sourced from a Marine-Protected Area off the coast of Nha Trang Bay, Vietnam - one of the most pristine and coveted bays in the world. Our local team collects the sea moss in the wild and dries it under the sun right on the shore, ensuring the highest quality and sustainability.

We take the safety and quality of our product seriously, and that's why we have all the necessary documents from our supplier, including the certificate of origin, Phytosanitary certificate, and Certificate of Analysis. Furthermore, our products have been checked by the FDA at the customs to ensure they meet the highest standards.

settings.question: What if you have serious diseases?
settings.answer: At the moment no dark side effects of sea moss have been identified, however, in case of any diseases, especially in the active stage, we advise you to contact your GP for an initial consultation regarding the intake of sea moss.

settings.question: How to use sea moss gel?
settings.answer: You can easily add our True Sea Moss gel into your routine and just eat 2 tablespoons a day after the meal. Also you can cook it however you like : add it in smoothies, desserts or juices.

settings.question: How could I use sea moss for skin?
settings.answer:
We recommend a wildcrafted gel, which has no fruit in its composition, for application to the skin. However, we believe that taking sea moss internally greatly accelerates the process of skin regeneration and the reduction of all imperfections. The main benefit of sea moss is that taking it internally has a beneficial effect on the whole body, not just the skin, as all the nutrients and vitamins are taken internally.

If you want to take sea moss both internally and externally, we advise you to take 2 jars: wildcrafted one and with any flavor.

settings.question: Can I use sea moss while breastfeeding or being pregnant?
settings.answer: We do not recommend sea moss for breastfeeding and pregnant women without consulting with a therapist. This is a particularly delicate period in the life of a woman and her body, so it is better to coordinate activities regarding the health of you and the baby.
